if you think kurdish culture in erbil is cool than you definitely haven’t been to a mukrani kurdish city especially mahabad. actually the kurdish culture in bashur is quite assimilated with the neighboring arab culture while the mukrani (which is in rojhelat) region of kurdistan is the least assimilated and having only a little bit of influence from persians such as proper sanitary and certain types of art. we also still wear the medieval style of kurdish dresses. mahabad is a city of amazing history and harbors a beautiful mountainous scenery, however the city is not found on any online map due to iran’s political fear however you can still find it on satellite maps such as google earth as a visibly urban yet unlabeled area of north western iran. also kurdish villages (in general not just in mukran) are usually the most authentic and traditional places in kurdistan to visit. one more thing, if you go done the road in mahabad, the east side of the mahabad dam, you will find the BEST villages and amazing fish farms. take mukran as a visit ☀️
